TITLE: Signing In a User with Email and Password (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet demonstrates the usage of the `signIn.email` function to sign in a user using their email and password.  It includes optional parameters like callbackURL and rememberMe. Callbacks can be defined to handle the sign-in process.
SOURCE: https://github.com/better-auth/better-auth/blob/main/docs/content/docs/basic-usage.mdx#_snippet_3

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const { data, error } = await authClient.signIn.email({
        /**
         * The user email
         */
        email,
        /**
         * The user password
         */
        password,
        /**
         * A URL to redirect to after the user verifies their email (optional)
         */
        callbackURL: "/dashboard",
        /**
         * remember the user session after the browser is closed. 
         * @default true
         */
        rememberMe: false
}, {
    //callbacks
})
```

