TITLE: Verify API Key (Server - TS)
DESCRIPTION: This code shows how to verify an API key using the `auth.api.verifyApiKey` method. It sends the API key in the `body` and checks for validity. The snippet also includes the ability to verify the key against required permissions, checking whether the API key has specific permissions for certain resources.
SOURCE: https://github.com/better-auth/better-auth/blob/main/docs/content/docs/plugins/api-key.mdx#_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const { valid, error, key } = await auth.api.verifyApiKey({
  body: {
    key: "your_api_key_here",
  },
});

//with permissions check
const { valid, error, key } = await auth.api.verifyApiKey({
  body: {
    key: "your_api_key_here",
    permissions: {
      projects: ["read", "read-write"]
    }
  },
});
```

