TITLE: Next.js Route Handler Setup
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to set up a route handler in a Next.js application using Better Auth. It imports the `auth` object (assumed to be configured elsewhere) and `toNextJsHandler` from the `better-auth/next-js` package to handle authentication requests at the `/api/auth/[...all]` route.
SOURCE: https://github.com/better-auth/better-auth/blob/main/docs/content/docs/installation.mdx#_snippet_14

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { auth } from "@/lib/auth"; // path to your auth file
import { toNextJsHandler } from "better-auth/next-js";

export const { POST, GET } = toNextJsHandler(auth);
```

