TITLE: Connecting Better Auth with PostgreSQL using Node.js
DESCRIPTION: This snippet demonstrates how to initialize Better Auth with a PostgreSQL database connection using the 'pg' package. It creates a Pool connection with a connection string containing the database credentials.
SOURCE: https://github.com/better-auth/better-auth/blob/main/docs/content/docs/adapters/postgresql.mdx#2025-04-22_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { betterAuth } from "better-auth";
import { Pool } from "pg";

export const auth = betterAuth({
  database: new Pool({
    connectionString: "postgres://user:password@localhost:5432/database",
  }),
});
```

