TITLE: Configuring Database Hooks with Better Auth in Typescript
DESCRIPTION: This example demonstrates how to configure database lifecycle hooks for user creation and update operations in the `better-auth` library. It shows how to define `before` and `after` hooks to modify user data or perform actions before and after database operations, such as adding a custom field during user creation or updating the `updatedAt` field before updating user data. These hooks offer customization points for database interactions.
SOURCE: https://github.com/better-auth/better-auth/blob/main/docs/content/docs/reference/options.mdx#_snippet_17

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { betterAuth } from "better-auth";
export const auth = betterAuth({
	databaseHooks: {
		user: {
			create: {
				before: async (user) => {
					// Modify user data before creation
					return { data: { ...user, customField: "value" } };
				},
				after: async (user) => {
					// Perform actions after user creation
				}
			},
			update: {
				before: async (userData) => {
					// Modify user data before update
					return { data: { ...userData, updatedAt: new Date() } };
				},
				after: async (user) => {
					// Perform actions after user update
				}
			}
		},
		session: {
			// Session hooks
		},
		account: {
			// Account hooks
		},
		verification: {
			// Verification hooks
		}
	},
})
```

