TITLE: Configure beforeDelete Callback in Better Auth
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to configure the `beforeDelete` callback in Better Auth. This callback is executed before a user is deleted and can be used for cleanup or additional checks.  APIError can be thrown to prevent user deletion.
SOURCE: https://github.com/better-auth/better-auth/blob/main/docs/content/docs/concepts/users-accounts.mdx#_snippet_12

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
export const auth = betterAuth({
    user: {
        deleteUser: {
            enabled: true,
            beforeDelete: async (user) => {
                // Perform any cleanup or additional checks here
            },
        },
    },
});
```

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
import { betterAuth } from "better-auth";
import { APIError } from "better-auth/api";

export const auth = betterAuth({
    user: {
        deleteUser: {
            enabled: true,
            beforeDelete: async (user, request) => {
                if (user.email.includes("admin")) {
                    throw new APIError("BAD_REQUEST", {
                        message: "Admin accounts can't be deleted",
                    });
                }
            },
