TITLE: Restrict Organization Creation (TypeScript)
DESCRIPTION: This code snippet shows how to restrict organization creation based on a user's subscription plan. The `allowUserToCreateOrganization` option is set to an async function that checks the user's subscription and returns a boolean indicating whether the user is allowed to create an organization. A `getSubscription` function is assumed to exist to retrieve user subscription data.
